FBIS3-22911 "jptot008__l94011" JPRS-TOT-94-008-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 1 March 1994 AFRICA SOMALIA Two Italian Aid Workers Kidnapped for Ransom Ransom Demand for Kidnapped Italians LD1302181194 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1750 GMT 13 Feb 94 LD1302181194 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext Language: Italian Article Type:BFN [Text] The bandits who kidnapped the two Italian aid workers have made a ransom demand. The terms of the demand have not yet been released. The news was communicated by Marco Benassi, director of the European Agricultural Training Consortium [CEFA], who received the news in a telex sent from CEFA's office in Mogadishu. Benassi said that the kidnapping of Gianfranco Stefani and Sergio Passadore was "a new way of extorting money."
